{
  "stem": "8892.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So I-- and Eva Lefkowicz from Olaszliszka looking for their aunts in Detroit.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Sure enough, I put that note in her letter.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Her friend, because Hungarians knew each other in here, too, OK, way back.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Her sister-in-law and my first cousin-- the one in here, Irene, who's deceased by now-- they knew each other.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "This girl calls her up and say, Irene, do you have a cousin Lefkowicz, Eva?",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And she screamed.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "She says, yes.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Of course, they didn't know me, because when my aunt came to this country, that's when I was born, 1928.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And but the other cousin, Margaret, who was home, she knew me as a 10-year-old little whiny kid who was always running after her.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And she gets the note, and, and I write to her that I'm looking for-- we are liberated, we're alive, we are-- we even wrote to you from Bergen-Belsen.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "Do you know, she went to the Lynnwood Post Office and our letter from my sister was there?",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And she thought that I'm in Sweden with my-- and I write that I'm in Sweden, and I don't know the rest of the family, who's alive or who not, and please, I would like to come to America.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And on Friday night, already by that time, we go to swim in there and we get into that group of socializing.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They're giving us-- showing movies, teaching us English, teaching us Swedish, and you have a sort of a normal life.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And on Friday night-- I never forget-- we're in line.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we had a huge dining room in there too, but it wasn't, you know, nothing like camp.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "It was like-- it's really a summer resort, beautiful dining room.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
